Ex. No: 9 — Group and Aggregate Data in Pandas using groupby()
Aim

To group and aggregate data using Pandas groupby() function.

Theory

Grouping divides data into categories and aggregation performs calculations like mean, sum, and count.

Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / IDLE / Google Colab
•
Pandas Library

Program
import pandas as pd

# Creating DataFrame
data = {
    'Department': ['AI&DS', 'CSE', 'AI&DS', 'ECE', 'CSE', 'AI&DS'],
    'Student': ['Ravi', 'Anu', 'Kumar', 'Divya', 'Arun', 'Meena'],
    'Marks': [88, 92, 79, 85, 90, 95]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("Original DataFrame:")
print(df)

# Mean marks
print("\nAverage Marks:")
print(df.groupby('Department')['Marks'].mean())

# Student count
print("\nStudent Count:")
print(df.groupby('Department')['Student'].count())

# Multiple aggregations
print("\nAggregations:")
print(df.groupby('Department')['Marks'].agg(['min', 'max', 'mean', 'sum']))



